 <text>
  <front>
   <head>SONNET TO HOPE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">O,  skilled to wear the form we love!</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To bid the shapes of fear and grief depart;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Come, gentle Hope! with one gay smile remove</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The lasting sadness of an aching heart.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thy voice, benign Enchantress! let me hear;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Say that for me some pleasures yet shall bloom, —</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">That Fancy's radiance, Friendship's precious tear,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Shall soften, or shall chase, misfortune's gloom.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But come not glowing in the dazzling ray,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Which once with dear illusions charm'd my eye, —</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">O! strew no more, sweet flatterer! on my way</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The flowers I fondly thought too bright to die;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Visions less fair will soothe my pensive breast,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">That asks not happiness, but longs for rest!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
